pageContext.claim: “In one case, I think they said, in New Jersey, we had 175,000 people show up for an arena that holds 9,000 people. And they showed up. And the reporters even reported that.”
pageContext.analysis: As usual, Trump is wildly inflating the attendance at one of his rallies. Trump officials said 175,000 people registered online for free tickets to the event. But that doesn't mean they all showed up. The venue was packed with more than 7,000 attendees in Wildwood, N.J., and "several thousand" more were outside, according to NJ Advance Media.
